      "content": "i get that, but it feels like the bill is just setting those towns up to fail. if the transition to green energy is basically inevitable anyway, wouldn't it be more logical to just stop subsidizing the \"old\" way of doing things and focus on the future? doesn't it make sense to just lean into what's actually working?",
